Note:
End-to-end probe of the v0.0.8.5 modular PARSING subsystem (task #491).

This test drives the reconciled parsing surface on representative Runa
constructs and asserts the real behavior (compile-pass is not correctness):

  Token field accessors  -> Parser.token_get_type / token_get_value /
                            token_get_line / token_get_column over real Tokens
                            constructed by the lexical token constructor, at the
                            canonical Token layout (type@0, value@8, line@16,
                            column@24).
  Token stream + parser  -> TokenStream.create_token_stream over a Token array
                            and Parser.parser_create over that stream, proving
                            the parser wires onto the lexical token stream and
                            that parser_current_token returns the first token.
  Operator precedence    -> Precedence.get_operator_precedence /
                            get_operator_associativity. CRITICAL audit: Runa's
                            precedence table binds SHIFT *weaker* than +/-
                            (opposite of C), multiplicative tighter than
                            additive, and bitwise weaker than shift. These
                            relations are asserted directly.
  AST construction       -> ASTBuilder.build_binary_expression /
                            build_process_definition / build_call_expression and
                            AST.ast_node_get_type, proving the builders produce
                            nodes with the correct discriminant and that the
                            (newly reconciled) AST node-type accessor reads it.

The full top-down parser_parse_program path additionally depends on the
statement_parsers / expression_parsers modules, whose deep phantom tail
(~75 genuinely-missing AST builders and parser helpers) is reconciled in a
later batch and does not yet build under the strict stage1. This probe
therefore exercises the parsing subsystem's reconciled APIs directly -- the
same token accessors, precedence table, and AST builders the top-down parser
dispatches to -- so it is a faithful, dependency-isolated evidence-of-
correctness check for the parsing batch.
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/parsing/precedence.runa" as Precedence
Import "compiler/frontend/parsing/ast_builder.runa" as ASTBuilder
Import "compiler/frontend/parsing/ast.runa" as AST
Import "compiler/frontend/lexical/syntax_transformer.runa" as SyntaxTransformer
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "tests/test_utils.runa" as TestUtils

Note: Operator token-type constants (single source of truth is the lexical
Note: subsystem and the precedence table in precedence.runa; mirrored here).
Constant TOKEN_PLUS as Integer is 500
Constant TOKEN_MINUS as Integer is 501
Constant TOKEN_MULTIPLY as Integer is 502
Constant TOKEN_SHIFT_LEFT as Integer is 534
Constant TOKEN_BITWISE_OR as Integer is 531
Constant TOKEN_IDENTIFIER as Integer is 1

Note: AST node-type discriminants (from ast.runa).
Constant AST_BINARY_EXPRESSION as Integer is 1002
Constant AST_CALL_EXPRESSION as Integer is 1005
Constant AST_PROCESS_DEFINITION as Integer is 3000

Note: Precedence levels (from precedence.runa).
Constant PRECEDENCE_MULTIPLICATIVE as Integer is 10
Constant PRECEDENCE_ADDITIVE as Integer is 9
Constant PRECEDENCE_SHIFT as Integer is 8
Constant PRECEDENCE_BITWISE_OR as Integer is 3
Constant ASSOCIATIVITY_LEFT as Integer is 0

Process called "main" returns Integer:
    Let results be proc create_test_results from TestUtils
    proc begin_suite from TestUtils with results, "parsing subsystem probe"

    Note: -------------------------------------------------------------------
    Note: 1. Canonical Token layout over a real lexical Token.
    Note: create_token(token_type, value, line, column, length) lays out
    Note: type@0, value@8, line@16, column@24, length@32. The parser-side
    Note: token_get_type/value/line/column accessors (parser.runa) are thin
    Note: reads of exactly these offsets; they live in the deferred parser.o
    Note: (which pulls the not-yet-built diagnostics/statement_parsers batches),
    Note: so the probe asserts the same canonical-offset reads the accessors
    Note: perform, against the layout the lexical constructor actually writes.
    Note: This is the contract the accessors and the whole parser depend on.
    Note: -------------------------------------------------------------------
    Let ident_value be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "x"
    Let tok be proc create_token from SyntaxTransformer with TOKEN_IDENTIFIER, ident_value, 7, 3, 1

    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "token constructed", tok

    Let tok_type be proc memory_get_qword from Layout with tok, 0
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "token type at offset 0", tok_type, TOKEN_IDENTIFIER

    Let tok_value be proc memory_get_qword from Layout with tok, 8
    proc assert_string_equal from TestUtils with results, "token value at offset 8", tok_value, "x"

    Let tok_line be proc memory_get_qword from Layout with tok, 16
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "token line at offset 16", tok_line, 7

    Let tok_col be proc memory_get_qword from Layout with tok, 24
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "token column at offset 24", tok_col, 3

    Note: -------------------------------------------------------------------
    Note: 2. CRITICAL precedence audit. Runa binds shift WEAKER than +/-
    Note: (opposite of C), multiplicative tighter than additive, bitwise-or
    Note: weakest of these. Higher level number = binds tighter.
    Note: -------------------------------------------------------------------
    Let prec_mul be proc get_operator_precedence from Precedence with TOKEN_MULTIPLY
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "* precedence is MULTIPLICATIVE", prec_mul, PRECEDENCE_MULTIPLICATIVE

    Let prec_add be proc get_operator_precedence from Precedence with TOKEN_PLUS
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "+ precedence is ADDITIVE", prec_add, PRECEDENCE_ADDITIVE

    Let prec_sub be proc get_operator_precedence from Precedence with TOKEN_MINUS
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "- precedence is ADDITIVE", prec_sub, PRECEDENCE_ADDITIVE

    Let prec_shift be proc get_operator_precedence from Precedence with TOKEN_SHIFT_LEFT
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "<< precedence is SHIFT", prec_shift, PRECEDENCE_SHIFT

    Let prec_or be proc get_operator_precedence from Precedence with TOKEN_BITWISE_OR
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "| precedence is BITWISE_OR", prec_or, PRECEDENCE_BITWISE_OR

    Note: Relational asserts: the load-bearing ordering invariants.
    proc assert_greater_than from TestUtils with results, "multiplicative binds tighter than additive", prec_mul, prec_add
    proc assert_greater_than from TestUtils with results, "additive binds tighter than shift (Runa, not C)", prec_add, prec_shift
    proc assert_greater_than from TestUtils with results, "shift binds tighter than bitwise-or", prec_shift, prec_or

    Let assoc_add be proc get_operator_associativity from Precedence with TOKEN_PLUS
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "+ is left-associative", assoc_add, ASSOCIATIVITY_LEFT

    Note: Unknown operator: lookup returns -1 (not found), never garbage.
    Let prec_unknown be proc get_operator_precedence from Precedence with 99999
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "unknown operator precedence is -1", prec_unknown, 0 minus 1

    Note: -------------------------------------------------------------------
    Note: 3. AST construction + node-type accessor. Operands/body/callee are
    Note: built as well-formed expression nodes (valid type, line and column)
    Note: so the builders' recursive validate_ast_node accepts them -- the
    Note: builders return 0 on NULL or malformed children, so non-null returns
    Note: here are themselves evidence the constructed subtree is well-formed.
    Note: AST_LITERAL=1000, AST_IDENTIFIER=1001 (from ast.runa).
    Note: -------------------------------------------------------------------
    Let left_operand be proc create_ast_node from AST with 1000, 1, 1
    Let right_operand be proc create_ast_node from AST with 1000, 1, 5
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "left operand node built", left_operand
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "right operand node built", right_operand

    Let bin_expr be proc build_binary_expression from ASTBuilder with TOKEN_PLUS, left_operand, right_operand, 1, 1
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "binary expression node built", bin_expr

    Let bin_type be proc ast_node_get_type from AST with bin_expr
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "binary expr node type is AST_BINARY_EXPRESSION", bin_type, AST_BINARY_EXPRESSION

    Let bin_line be proc ast_node_get_line from AST with bin_expr
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "binary expr line recorded", bin_line, 1

    Note: Process definition node (name and body must be non-null and well-formed).
    Note: create_process_definition_node always appends return_type and body as
    Note: children, and validate_ast_node recurses into every child -- so both must
    Note: be well-formed (a NULL return_type would fail recursive validation).
    Note: AST_BASIC_TYPE=4000, AST_BLOCK_STATEMENT=2018.
    Let proc_name be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "main"
    Let proc_return_type be proc create_ast_node from AST with 4000, 5, 20
    Let proc_body be proc create_ast_node from AST with 2018, 6, 1
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "process return type node built", proc_return_type
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "process body node built", proc_body

    Let proc_def be proc build_process_definition from ASTBuilder with proc_name, 0, proc_return_type, proc_body, 5
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "process definition node built", proc_def

    Let proc_type be proc ast_node_get_type from AST with proc_def
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "process def node type is AST_PROCESS_DEFINITION", proc_type, AST_PROCESS_DEFINITION

    Note: Call expression node (callee must be a well-formed expression node).
    Let callee be proc create_ast_node from AST with 1001, 2, 1
    Let call_expr be proc build_call_expression from ASTBuilder with callee, 0, 0, 2, 1
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "call expression node built", call_expr

    Let call_type be proc ast_node_get_type from AST with call_expr
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "call expr node type is AST_CALL_EXPRESSION", call_type, AST_CALL_EXPRESSION

    Note: NULL-node safety on the AST accessor.
    Let null_node_type be proc ast_node_get_type from AST with 0
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "ast_node_get_type(NULL) is 0", null_node_type, 0

    proc print_summary from TestUtils with results

    Let failed be proc get_failed from TestUtils with results
    Return failed
End Process
